  "base_commit": "c50028b1f332f6332965bdec95b2ca29b655f40c",
  "pr_number": 14548,
  "issue_number": 14551,
  "issue_title": "[Feature Request]: Moodle connector should support deleted-file sync",
  "issue_body": "### Self Checks\n\n- [x] I have searched for existing issues [search for existing issues](https://github.com/infiniflow/ragflow/issues), including closed ones.\n- [x] I confirm that I am using English to submit this report ([Language Policy](https://github.com/infiniflow/ragflow/issues/5910)).\n- [x] Non-english title submitions will be closed directly ( \u975e\u82f1\u6587\u6807\u9898\u7684\u63d0\u4ea4\u5c06\u4f1a\u88ab\u76f4\u63a5\u5173\u95ed ) ([Language Policy](https://github.com/infiniflow/ragflow/issues/5910)).\n- [x] Please do not modify this template :) and fill in all the required fields.\n\n### Is your feature request related to a problem?\n\n```Markdown\nYes. The Moodle connector does not let the sync runner clean up indexed documents that were deleted from the source.\n\nOther connectors such as dropbox, seafile, webdav, rss, gitlab, gmail, zendesk, asana, and bitbucket already do this through a slim snapshot pass. The connector returns a light list of every document id that still exists in the source, and the runner removes any indexed doc whose id is not in that list.\n\nMoodle is missing from this set. After a user deletes a resource, forum, page, book, assign, or quiz module in Moodle, the matching document stays in the dataset forever and shows up in retrieval results, even though the source is gone.\n```\n\n### Describe the feature you'd like\n\nThe Moodle connector should expose a slim snapshot pass so the sync runner can remove deleted modules from the index, the same way the other connectors do it.\n\nWhen the user turns on \"sync deleted files\" for a Moodle data source, the runner should:\n\n1. Walk every enrolled course and module in Moodle.\n2. Collect a list of slim document ids for every module that could be indexed (resource, forum, page, book, assign, quiz).\n3. Compare this list with the docs already in the index.\n4. Delete any indexed doc whose id is not in the list.\n\nThe snapshot must not download files. It only needs the module type and id, which is enough to build the slim id.\n\nThe option for \"sync deleted files\" should also show up in the web UI for Moodle, the same way it shows up for the other connectors that already support this.\n\n\n### Describe implementation you've considered\n\n_No response_\n\n### Documentation, adoption, use case\n\n```Markdown\nSame use case the other connectors solved already. A teacher or admin removes a course resource in Moodle, and the next sync run removes the matching chunks from the dataset. Retrieval no longer returns dead links for content that no longer exists at the source.\n\nNo new docs are needed. The sync deleted files toggle for Moodle behaves the same way it does for the other connectors that already expose it.\n```\n\n### Additional information\n\nThe fix follows the pattern already merged for these connectors:\n\n- feat(rss): support deleted-file sync (#14493)\n- feat(webdav): support deleted-file sync via slim snapshot (#14491)\n- feat(zendesk): support deleted-file sync (#14487)\n- feat(asana): support deleted-file sync (#14468)\n- feat(seafile): support deleted-file sync via slim snapshot (#14499)\n- feat(dropbox): support deleted-file sync (#14476)\n- Feat: enable sync deleted files in gitlab (#14481)\n- Feat: enable sync deleted files for Gmail (#14462)\n- Feat: sync deleted files in Bitbucket (#14450)\n",
  "merged_at": "2026-05-07T09:44:46.000Z",
